President Barack Obama has designated certain funding as emergency requirements in accordance with the Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2016. This designation applies to funding designated by Congress for the "International Monetary Programs -- United States Quota, International Monetary Fund -- Direct Loan Program Account," and "Loans to the International Monetary Fund -- Direct Loan Program Account." The President's action is based on the authority granted by section 251(b)(2)(A) of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act of 1985. The specific details of this action can be found in a memorandum from the Director of the Office of Management and Budget.